    "body": "### Problem\n\nPersistent undo doesn't automatically read undo files when editing lua files, if `:syntax on` is set before the persistent undo options.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n``` bash\n$ cat my.vim\n```\n\n```vim\n:syntax on\nif has('persistent_undo')\n  set undofile\n  set undodir=$HOME/.undo_dir\nendif\n```\n\nUse `./nvim-linux-arm64.appimage --clean -u my.vim foo.lua` to add some words into a new `foo.lua` file, save the buffer, exit.\n\nOpen again using `./nvim-linux-arm64.appimage --clean -u my.vim foo.lua`, press `u`, observe there is no undo history.\n\nComment out `:syntax on` or place it after `set undofile`, run `./nvim-linux-arm64.appimage --clean -u my.vim foo.lua` again, press `u`, observe that undo history was loaded.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nUndo history to be loaded regardless of file type or placement of `:syntax on`.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.11.0-dev-1897+g47cfe901d7\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.1 (2024 Jan 02, compiled May 03 2024 02:45:42)\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 15.3.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\niTerm 3.5.11\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nNightly build",
